@DentonGentry Some users have great reasons for running on-prem login servers for specific workloads (besides cost). That's a whole box of worms though to get into! 

Off-topic 2c: Official on-prem solution + client support for multiple login servers? Would definitely turn some of these users into paying customers.

Either way, multiple login servers (on iOS) will allow some orgs to dip their feet in Tailscale's tech. That's a start & a win :)

@tasdflkjweio You would have WRITE clients only connect to Node A, and READ clients connect to Node B + C. 
The node that you send the query is the node that executes it.
Note: Distributed (Sharded) tables do change this behavior, but this is not required for replication.

